        a(href="http://swyp.us") swyp.us
        | , exposing APIs, and allowing for the addition of large numbers of simultaneous users. 
      li People interested in improving the user-facing aspects of Sw&yuml;p, and capable of website interface development to promote more intuitive and reliable content transfer, and better 
